<table width="763" border="0">
      <tr>
        <td width="500" height="18" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#993333" class="box_titles">We didn't get mad, we just got even. <span class="box_titles_small">September 01, 2006, 10:19:38 PM by <a href="mailto:justju1ie@hotmail.com">Ravenne</a></span>		</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="763" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#996666" class="box_links">
		The purpose of this article is to address the slander threads that have started on the EQ2 forums regarding a recent contested 3 Prince encounter.<br /><br />On July 15th, 2006, Fires of Heaven experienced a disappointing turn of events during a Mutagenic Outcast raid.<br /><br />Fires of Heaven and Ghosts of War were both contesting MO.  With over 100 people in Bonemire, the lag was horrific.  Every attempt was a struggle.  After a failed attempt by GoW, FoH again pulled the encounter deciding it was their last attempt.  FoH killed MO, and all but one of his adds.  During the course of the fight the raid slowly wiped, and our last player went down leaving this final add up.<br /><br />GoW, standing by, decided to interfere with the game mechanics of this event, and pulled the last heroic add before the encounter re set.  They killed it, with their impressive raid force of 24, and their raid leader distributed the Master chest loot amongst their raid members, as if credit for the victory was entirely theirs.<br><br /><br><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/gowmo.jpg" alt="" /><br /><br><br /><br />FoH, understandably, was pissed, but we didn’t cause a huge public fuss over it.  A Dev did hear the whole story and that’s why the MO encounter was NERFED to hell.  Now almost any raiding guild can kill MO.<br /><br><br />On August 31st, the 3 Princes spawn, and 3 raiding guilds are gathering forces to contest the encounter.  GoW pulls first, and came SO close to beating it….<br><br /><br><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/gow3wipe.jpg" alt="" /><br><br /><br><br />When the encounter re set, FoH pulls it.  We also wipe.  We revive and fly back to the encounter and prep for our next attempt.  Meanwhile GoW pulls again, on their 2nd attempt.<br /><br />Their attempt lasted a long time.  They killed the adds, and 1 of the names, but their raid was slowly wiping and their dps and rezzers couldn’t keep up or make progress on the rest of the encounter.<br /><br />The way FoH saw this series of events was a perfect opportunity for a well deserved payback for the MO encounter of the previous month.  As GoW wiped and the mobs moved to re set, our raid intercepted it and engaged the 2 remaining named mobs.  Of course we beat it, and claimed the master chest for our guild.  Nice discovery too:<br><br /><br><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/3pdisco.jpg" alt="" /><br><br /><br><br />Now…Fires of Heaven, as a general rule, doesn’t like to roll this way.  However as a guild we felt that GoW should take a little of what they dished out.  It’s not as though they came ‘close’ on beating the encounter, though; they had 2 epic mobs left when they wiped.  (In contrast to the MO encounter where FoH left 1 heroic mob up)<br><br /><br><br /><img src="http://www.fohguild.org/eq2/phpnews/images/3princeloot.jpg" alt="" /><br><br /><br><br />To the credit (I guess) of GoW, they have thus far not started a bunch of shit talking or bitch festing over this matter.  This post is entirely directed at the posts of Defiance guild members or the questions of other people on the EQ2 forums.  As for Defiance; yeah, the situation kind of sucked for you guys.  We intended the entire effect for GoW.  It’s kind of funny; the fact that GoW is acting rather adult about the matter, but some Defiance members are stirring up shit and crying like 2 year olds.  *edited*
